This film is pure madness.

Brandon Cronenberg took one of his own frustrating trips and turned it into one of the most unhinged movies you’ll ever see.

Infinity Pool (2023), directed by Brandon Cronenberg and starring Alexander Skarsgård, Mia Goth, and Cleopatra Coleman, is one of the most unhinged, visually hypnotic films you’ll see in recent years. With its striking visuals, darkly provocative themes, and haunting performances, it’s a cinematic experience that’s weird, wild, and impossible to look away from — the kind of movie that stays with you long after the screen goes black.

